comparasion operator:
is C3 and D3 equal? 
=C3=D3

is C3 greater than D3?
=CS>D3
return a true or false statement

FUNCTIONS:
avg()
and() //takes logical parameters e.g. true or false values
count() 
countif()
countif(c3:c9,"<=5"), countif(c3:c9,"<="& I9)
- here, if the value of I9 changes, value of our cell changes too
- F4 (Fn+f4 for me) locks in referenced cells such that if value of said cells changes, our formula updates its attributes' values

IF statements 
IF(test_value //true or false or a conditional statment (c3=d3, return_value_for_true, return_value_for_false

IFS()
IFS(first condition, iftrue_return, second condition, if_true_return, TRUE/FALSE, default value)

2nd last attribute:
To specify a default result, enter TRUE for your final logical_test argument. 
If none of the other conditions are met, the corresponding value will be returned.



